<b>Great in Highhold Pass - </b>7/13/01 5:30:01 PM<br>~ <b>Smegley</b><blockquote>Whether soloing or grouping, this song rules when faced with numerous opponents.  I'm only level 19, so what an earlier post said about this being resisted at higher levels may be true.  If you're in an *experienced* group of players (not characters), that know what they're doing, this song makes taking on groups or orcs or gnolls a piece of cake.<br><br>One warning.  Make sure you have tanks that can taunt well.  Because if they can't, or just don't notice it, as soon as a mob wakes up, it's coming after YOU.  I died once when that happened.  Everyone else had almost a full bar of health at when I kicked it.  That's why it's good to group with people that know what they're doing.  Everybody needs to know what you're doing before hand.  That way they don't each attack a separate mob and wake them all up to attack you.  So get ready to zone then disband if your groupmates are bumbling incomps.  </blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
