<b>Look at them all sleep. - </b>5/3/01 11:40:59 AM<br>~ <b>Dalhari</b><blockquote>I used this song to help out newbies on orc hill in GFay and at times I had more that 8 mobs sleeping quietly.  From my experience with this song if you use a instrument it's unlimited on the number of mobs you can mez...   </blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Wonderful song... - </b>5/2/01 8:26:07 AM<br>~ <b>Bolil</b><blockquote>Just make sure your group knows what you are doing :)  Tell them over and over and over until they get it straight :)  Always /assist on the puller, always let the puller pick the next target once the first falls, then /assist again.<br><br>When I just got the song, I was fighting gnolls in East Karana.  The biggest problem I had was trying to get the group to coordinate their attacks when we had 3 or 4 gnolls on us :)  An overactive Warrior in the group kept attacking one of the additional gnolls, which would then aggro on me and backhand me upside the head :)  But after about 15 minutes, I had the fellow with an /assist hotkey, and the whole group was doing much better!  I can imagine how an Enchanter feels in this situation...at least I've got the AC and hitpoints to absorb some damage :)<br><br>In Santana mode (Mandolin equipped), it seemed that the song was a lot more effective.  Maybe it's subjective, but it seemed that the mesmerization failed a lot less, and that silly second resist also failed a lot less.  By twisting in a healing song, we were tearing through packs of gnolls at an alarming rate :)<br><br>Well, happy strumming all!<br><br>Bolil the Boy Bard<br><br></blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>It definitely does more than four. - </b>4/30/01 8:10:10 PM<br>~ <b>Morrilin</b><blockquote>This song is a *must* if you don't have an enchanter, especially if you don't have a puller who can reliably single pull, like an overzealous ranger friend of mine.  The most difficult part is once the mobs all turn on you, it takes a full pulse from singing to the mez effect, during which they're all aggro on you, and a stun means you start over again.  But, last night I did briefly have 8 out of 8 dazed goblins out for the count in Runnyeye, so it can be done.  However, if you're wielding weapons instead of instruments (which seems less and less like the wise course every time I think about it) don't bother.  All this is then is a tauntsong.  Stick with Bellow and some buffs if you like your stickypokes.  Then again, why did you pick a bard in the first place, then?  :)<br><br>Morrilin<br>Bard of the 23rd circle<br>Xegony server</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
